        <p class="metadata">Posted by Matthew Weier O'Phinney (matthew) on 2009-06-26T04:27:41.000+0000</p> 
        <div class="body">
            <p>You can turn on short_tags in your php.ini, apache configuration, or .htaccess file. In your php.ini, use the following:</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
short_open_tag = On
</code></pre>

<p>Within your apache configuration or .htaccess, use the following:</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
php_flag short_open_tag On
</code></pre>

<p>Regardless, you can also always use long tags: "&lt;?php" and "&lt;?php echo" will <em>always</em> work, even in your phtml files.</p>

